(B) In rural areas, (1) aid to small and medium farmers in form of technical
                    assistance and less restrictive bank credit; (2) encouragement to artisans; 
 (3) infrastructure, especially road
                    building;

(D) Foreign private investment probably will be moderately encouraged in those
                    areas which do not compete with, or are not considered threat to, Guatemalan
                    business community;
